        "subheadline": "Acne, eczema, and psoriasis are not skin diseases. They are inflammatory conditions driven by a broken gut barrier. When ancestral bacteria deplete — a documented pattern in immigrant and diaspora communities — your intestinal wall leaks endotoxins into your bloodstream. Your immune system responds. Your skin pays the price. No serum, steroid, or retinoid can fix what starts below the surface.",
